===2010 census===
The [[2010 United States census]] counted 1,421 people, 1,008 households, and 356 families in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|2050.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|}}. There were 1,234 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1780.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}. The racial makeup was 98.03% (1,393) [[White (U.S. census)|White]], 0.63% (9) [[Black (U.S. census)|Black or African American]], 0.00% (0) [[Native American (U.S. census)|Native American]], 0.56% (8) [[Asian (U.S. census)|Asian]], 0.00% (0) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.35% (5) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 0.42% (6) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. census)|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 1.76% (25) of the population.<ref name=Census2010>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3411140 DP-1 - Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data for Cedar Glen Lakes CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212134300/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3411140 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed January 11, 2013.</ref>

Of the 1,008 households, 0.1% had children under the age of 18; 29.2% were married couples living together; 5.4% had a female householder with no husband present and 64.7% were non-families. Of all households, 61.9% were made up of individuals and 53.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.41 and the average family size was 2.07.<ref name=Census2010/>

0.2% of the population were under the age of 18, 0.8% from 18 to 24, 1.8% from 25 to 44, 16.5% from 45 to 64, and 80.7% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 74.6 years. For every 100 females, the population had 60.6 males. For every 100 females ages 18 and older there were 60.6 males.<ref name=Census2010/>

===2000 census===
As of the [[2000 United States census]]<ref name="GR2" /> there were 1,617 people, 1,126 households, and 451 families living in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|931.8|/km2|/mi2|disp=preunit|people|people|abbr=on}}. There were 1,242 housing units at an average density of {{convert|715.7|/km2|/mi2|disp=preunit|units|units|abbr=on}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 98.52% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.68% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.06% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.43% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.19% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.12% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.30% of the population.<ref name=Census2000>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/00_SF1/DP1/1600000US3411140 DP-1 - Profile of General Demographic Characteristics: 2000 from the Census 2000 Summary File 1 (SF 1) 100-Percent Data for Cedar Glen Lakes CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212092210/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/00_SF1/DP1/1600000US3411140 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed January 11, 2013.</ref>

There were 1,126 households, of which 0.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 36.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 3.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 59.9% were non-families. 58.5% of all households were made up of individuals, and 53.3% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.44 and the average family size was 2.05.<ref name=Census2000/>

In the CDP the population was spread out, with 0.2% under the age of 18, 0.1% from 18 to 24, 2.0% from 25 to 44, 15.8% from 45 to 64, and 82.0% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 75 years. For every 100 females, there were 58.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 58.7 males.<ref name=Census2000/>

The median income for a household in the CDP was $20,378, and the median income for a family was $30,278. Males had a median income of $40,368 versus $35,833 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $20,246. About 1.9% of families and 3.7% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including none of those under age 18 and 3.1% of those age 65 or over.<ref name=Census2000/>

